The paper proposes a system for training node embeddings, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining. The system is designed to handle large-scale networks with tens of millions or even hundreds of millions of nodes, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of Large Scale Learning (cs.LG), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Among these categories, cs.LG is the most likely one, as it is specifically related to machine learning and covers topics such as neural networks and deep learning, which are relevant to the paper. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve topics such as parallel computing, data management, and algorithms, which are important for developing efficient systems for large-scale node embedding.
